            <aside class="quote no-group" data-username="RopeStringFace" data-post="5" data-topic="2122">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="https://forum.throneoflies.com/user_avatar/forum.throneoflies.com/ropestringface/40/1106_2.png" class="avatar"> RopeStringFace:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Why not?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>Because it’s toxic for the game balance, the whole point of Neutral Killers in any Mafia game is to serve as a secondary antagonist to keep both the protagonist and primary antagonist on their toes, if they are convertable they simply stop being any sort of threat to the primary antagonist</p>
<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="RopeStringFace" data-post="5" data-topic="2122">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="https://forum.throneoflies.com/user_avatar/forum.throneoflies.com/ropestringface/40/1106_2.png" class="avatar"> RopeStringFace:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>Killing third parties in an attempt to kill the second party is still a threat to the third party.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>See my previous answer about the place of an NK, this class is not an antagonist it’s a mild<br>
nuisance</p>
<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="RopeStringFace" data-post="5" data-topic="2122">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt="" width="20" height="20" src="https://forum.throneoflies.com/user_avatar/forum.throneoflies.com/ropestringface/40/1106_2.png" class="avatar"> RopeStringFace:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>first off, there is not “like” a maximum of two Nks. There IS a maximum of two NKs.) It does not waste these spots. The gladiator kills very often.</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>if you’ve got to correct my grammatical errors it proves your argument is strong, and it doesn’t matter how often it kills IT IS NOT SERVING ITS PURPOSE</p>
          <p><a href="https://forum.throneoflies.com/t/deleted-the-gladiator/2122/9">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
